==Description== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
The '''Std DockOverlayToggleBottom''' command provides a shortcut to quickly show or hide the entire group of panels that are currently in the [[Std_DockOverlayAll|overlay system]] on the bottom side of the screen.

<!--T:5-->
This command does not move panels into or out of the overlay system; it only toggles the visibility of the bottom overlay container itself. This is a convenience feature for users who want to temporarily hide all panels on one side of the view to maximize their workspace without having to exit the overlay mode completely.

==Usage== <!--T:6-->

<!--T:7-->
# The [[Std_DockOverlayAll|overlay mode]] must be active, and there must be at least one panel in the bottom overlay area.
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|View → Overlay Docked Panel → Toggle Bottom}} option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|Ctrl}}+{{KEY|Down}}.
#* Use the overlay toggle bottom button ([[File:Std_DockOverlayToggleBottom.svg|16px]]) from a docked window's title bar.


